  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "REGIONAL SALES MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description: </strong></u><br /><br />We are looking for a <strong>Regional Sales Manager</strong> to support <strong>category growth, product launches, and regional initiatives</strong> across multiple markets. This role works closely with country\nteams, regional teams, and global brand partners.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Regional Category & Growth Support</strong></p><ul><li>Support development and execution of regional category strategies for consumer health and lifestyle products</li><li>Analyze market performance, consumer behavior, and competitive dynamics across\ncountries to identify transferable growth opportunities</li><li>Consolidate cross-market insights and best practices to inform regional playbooks and\nrollouts</li></ul><p><strong>Go-to-Market & Launch Execution</strong></p><ul><li>Support  regional go-to-market planning for new products and categories, including\nlaunch frameworks and execution guidelines</li><li>Coordinate with country teams to adapt regional strategies to local market conditions</li><li>Track launch performance and key metrics across markets to support optimization\nand scaling</li></ul><p><strong>Brand & Partner Coordination</strong></p><ul><li>Support evaluation and coordination with global and regional brand partners</li><li>Assist with commercial planning, alignment on pricing and positioning, and launch\nreadiness across markets</li><li>Support ongoing performance reviews and follow-ups with partners and internal\nstakeholders</li></ul><p><strong>Regional Coordination & Enablement</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with country commercial, marketing, and operations teams to ensure\nalignment on regional initiatives</li><li>Develop regional materials, reports, and updates for management and stakeholders</li><li>Support knowledge sharing and capability building across markets</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li>5–10 years of experience in commercial, growth, strategy, or category\nmanagement roles</li><li>Experience working on regional or cross-market initiatives in consumer-facing\n industries</li><li>Exposure to consumer electronics, lifestyle products, health & wellness, or\nadjacent categories</li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>Strong analytical and structured thinking</li><li>Ability to translate insights into practical execution guidelines</li><li>Comfortable working across multiple markets, teams, and stakeholders</li><li>Strong communication and coordination skills</li></ul><p><strong>Regional Mindset</strong></p><ul><li>Experience leveraging learnings from one market to scale in others</li><li>Comfortable balancing regional consistency with local flexibility</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
